[These articles tell us what type of ticks but neither tells us which
specific disease. Ticks carry and transmit a variety of diseases. The
specific tick is often associated with a particular disease. The 2nd
article indicates the _Ixodes_ sp. is highest on the likely list of
possibilities (leading to tick paralysis); but there is no official
realease of a diagnosis. But clearly the disease is known if an
anti-serum is being given. Hopefully additional information will be
forthcoming. - Mod.TG]

[The interactive HealthMap/ProMED map for Queensland is available at:
http://healthmap.org/r/1kJr - CopyEd.EJP]
